arch:property.oc:show_val: The bone from this unit is moderately fragmented, the majority of the bone is unidentifiable long bone shaft fragments and rib pieces. Sheep/goat dominate the identifiable portion but there are a few pieces of cattle skull. Some bone has been digested and burnt bone is present in low proportions that is generally represented by carbonised fragments. One piece of bird was recovered from the dry sieve. Flotation sample #1 contained a number of teeth of what was probably the same caprine maxilla from a subadult. A few fish bones were also retrieved from this sample. Last number = 118
